Case Study on marketing analyst team at Bellabeat  for Coursera Data Analytics Course
Srividhya S H
05/08/2022
This case study/publication is part of the capstone project under Google-Coursera’s Data Analytics course. 
Meanwhile, comments/feedback on this case study are more than welcome and greatly appreciate

Case Study Roadmap 
Guiding questions :
● What is the problem you are trying to solve? 
 I will explore to focus on one of Bellabeat’s products and analyze smart device data to gain insight into how consumers are using their smart devices.

● How can your insights drive business decisions?
. The insights you discover will then help guide marketing strategy for the company. You will present your analysis to the Bellabeat executive team along with your high-level recommendations for Bellabeat’s marketing strategy
What is the problem you are trying to solve? 
To analyze smart device usage data in order to gain insight into how consumers use non-Bellabeat smart devices.
Key tasks 
1. Identify the business task 
Analyze and unlock new growth opportunities for the company by  analyzing smart device usage data in order to gain insight into how consumers use non-Bellabeat smart devices.
 One Bellabeat product to apply these insights to in your presentation
My goal is to look at datasets to find out:
•	How are customers using other fitness trackers, in their daily life?
•	What particular features seem to be the most heavily used?
•	What features do Bellabeat products already have that consumers want, and how do we focus marketing on those aspects?

R programming is used to complete my casestudy.
